1
00:00:00,750 --> 00:00:02,958
There were many people inside

2
00:00:03,041 --> 00:00:04,583
I’ll now list the ones I remember

3
00:00:05,291 --> 00:00:08,458
Among my relatives were my brothers

4
00:00:08,958 --> 00:00:12,416
Abdullah, Abdul Hakim, and Muhammad al-Salamah

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,375
And my father, Khalaf al-Salamah

6
00:00:15,250 --> 00:00:17,083
And my cousin Abdullah Hassan al-Salamah

7
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:20,291
And my other cousins

8
00:00:20,500 --> 00:00:23,291
Abdul Musleh Hassan al-Ibrahim

9
00:00:23,791 --> 00:00:26,416
And Hammouda and Ahmad Hassan al-Ibrahim

10
00:00:26,875 --> 00:00:28,708
And Abdul Hakim Hassan al-Ibrahim

11
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,500
Aziz Hassan al-Ibrahim

12
00:00:34,875 --> 00:00:37,375
Ahmad Hassan—I think I already mentioned him

13
00:00:38,916 --> 00:00:40,666
And Faraj Hassan al-Ibrahim

14
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:45,458
And their sons, Hassan Ibrahim al-Hassan

15
00:00:46,125 --> 00:00:47,458
Faraj Ibrahim al-Hassan

16
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:49,750
And Muhammad Faraj al-Hassan

17
00:00:51,166 --> 00:00:54,500
And Muhammad Abdul Fattah al-Oweihi, my cousin

18
00:00:55,291 --> 00:00:58,208
And Kamal Abdul Fattah al-Oweihi

19
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:03,708
From Jarniya, there was Walid al-Haji

20
00:01:04,208 --> 00:01:06,625
And Muasstam and Hamada al-Haji

21
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:15,958
There was also a young man named
Anis, a relative of ours from the area

22
00:01:17,583 --> 00:01:21,875
As well as others who had been imprisoned before us

23
00:01:22,125 --> 00:01:23,541
Including Muhannad al-Raji

24
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,250
Ahmad al-Laji and Faisal al-Zahir

25
00:01:27,666 --> 00:01:28,666
Ahmad al-Hamoud

26
00:01:29,375 --> 00:01:33,083
And people from Raqqa Prison, among them Ahmad Sinu

27
00:01:33,666 --> 00:01:35,083
And a young man named Hamad

28
00:01:35,958 --> 00:01:39,791
And young men from the al-Hutayl clan in Mansoura

29
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:43,125
I don’t remember their names

30
00:01:43,416 --> 00:01:47,208
Because their names were similar to ours

31
00:01:47,375 --> 00:01:49,708
And I started getting confused from so many names

32
00:01:50,125 --> 00:01:55,416
There were also friends of mine in prison

33
00:01:55,875 --> 00:01:57,958
Harith Haj Abdul Sheikh

34
00:01:58,458 --> 00:02:01,625
And Faisal Saad Rajoub from Homs

35
00:02:02,291 --> 00:02:05,916
And Khaled al-Harbi, a young man from Tabqa

36
00:02:06,875 --> 00:02:10,458
And a young man from Rural Aleppo named Alaa

37
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,458
But he was killed in prison

38
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:16,125
There were also foreign prisoners

39
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:19,875
Affiliated with ISIS, but they never told me their names

40
00:02:20,041 --> 00:02:21,958
They all went by noms de guerre like Abu so-and-so

41
00:02:22,083 --> 00:02:24,791
Among them were Saudis

42
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:29,208
And a Lebanese-born man with German citizenship

43
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:34,541
He had been wounded by a gunshot from one of his comrades

44
00:02:34,791 --> 00:02:36,166
And had metal rods in his body

45
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:39,375
There were six foreign prisoners in total

46
00:02:40,208 --> 00:02:43,291
Because they were against the idea of establishing the Islamic State

47
00:02:43,458 --> 00:02:46,458
They had criticized it, so they were imprisoned
